contentrichtext.text: '''QL''' may refer to: * [[QL (chemical)]], the chemical isopropyl aminoethylmethyl phosphonite, a precursor to the nerve agent VX (NATO code) * [[.QL]], an object-oriented query language used to retrieve data from relational database management systems * [[Query language]], computer languages used to make queries into databases and information systems * Bedford QL, a three-ton military 4x4 truck by [[Bedford Vehicles]] * Philips QL, an induction lighting system by Philips, see [[electrodeless lamp]] * [[Sinclair QL]], a 1980s home and personal computer by Sinclair Research Ltd * ''[[Quake Live]]'', a 2010 first-person shooter video game in development by id Software * [[Queen Latifah]] (born 1970), American rapper * [[Aero Lanka]] (IATA airline designator: QL) * ''[[Quantum Leap (TV series)]], a television program * [[Quadratus lumborum muscle]], a muscle in the lower back * ''[[Le Québécois Libre]]'', a political webzine * [[ATCvet code QL]] (''Antineoplastic and immunomodulating agents''), a section of the Anatomical Therapeutic Chemical Classification System for veterinary medicinal products {{disambiguation}}
